.TH server 1  "server " 
.SH NAME
server \- Start debug server for remote connections
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBserver\fR [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-port\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-token\fR] [\fB\-\-tls\-cert\fR] [\fB\-\-tls\-key\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Start debug server for remote connections
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-port\fR \fI<PORT>\fR [default: 9229]
Port to listen on
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-token\fR \fI<TOKEN>\fR
Authentication token (optional, if not provided no auth required)
.TP
\fB\-\-tls\-cert\fR \fI<TLS_CERT>\fR
TLS certificate file path (optional)
.TP
\fB\-\-tls\-key\fR \fI<TLS_KEY>\fR
TLS private key file path (optional)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
\fBClients cannot connect\fR
Verify the server is listening on the intended port and that loopback, firewall, container, or CI networking policy allows inbound TCP on that interface.
.TP
\fBAuthentication failures\fR
If you set \fB\-\-token\fR, every client must present the same token. Fix token mismatch before changing retry or timeout settings.
.TP
\fBProtocol mismatch reports\fR
Use matching client and server builds. Mixing a newer extension or CLI client with an older server can fail during handshake.
.TP
\fBTimeout complaints from clients\fR
The server may be healthy but slow for a specific request type. Ask clients to increase their per\-request timeout knobs before broadening all retry windows.
